age":{"title":"age","type":"object","properties":{"strategy_name":{"title":"Strategy Name","enum":["age"],"type":"string","const":"age"},"seconds":{"title":"Seconds","type":"integer","default":3600}},"description":"age -\nBuffy will redownload when the cached version has a certain age in seconds. The default age is 3600sec\nThis is usefull for dynamic remote resources, where the webserver wont provide any informations about the state of the resource like \"etag\", \"last_modified_datetime\" or \"size_in_bytes\"\n\nparams:\n    seconds - int - default: 3600 - The duration a resource will be cached until it gets a redownload from the source"},"cron":{"title":"cron","type":"object","properties":{"strategy_name":{"title":"Strategy Name","enum":["cron"],"type":"string","const":"cron"},"cron":{"title":"Cron","type":"string","default":"0 0 * * *"},"run_at_start":{"title":"Run At Start","type":"boolean","default":true}},"description":"cron - Strategy\nBuffy will redownload the remote resource in an certain interval. Defined in the Linux cron format.\nSimilar to the \"age\"-Strategy, but allows more flexibility for more complex situations.\nThis is usefull for dynamic remote resources, where the webserver wont provide any informations about the state of the resource like \"etag\", \"last_modified_datetime\" or \"size_in_bytes\"\n\nparams:\n    cron - str - a standard cron definition https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron\n\n    run_at_start - bool - regardless of the cron schedule, Buffy will redownload the resource once when Buffy just started"},"never":{"title":"never","type":"object","properties":{"strategy_name":{"title":"Strategy Name","enum":["never"],"type":"string","const":"never"}},"description":"never -\nOnce downlaoded we will serve only this cached file. no matter how often it is requested.\nThis is usefull for files that will be 100% static."},"when_remote_changed":{"title":"when_remote_changed","type":"object","properties":{"strategy_name":{"title":"Strategy Name","enum":["when_remote_changed"],"type":"string","const":"when_remote_changed"},"check_interval_sec":{"title":"Check Interval Sec","type":"integer","default":43200}},"description":"when_remote_changed  - Strategy\nBuffy will ask the webserver of the remote resource about the state of the resource.\nVia \"etag\", \"last_modified_datetime\" or \"size_in_bytes\" Buffy can determine if the resource changed.\nIf it has changed Buffy will download and cache the newer version.\nThis is usefull for scenarios where the client need to have the newest version instant and reliable available.\n\nparams:\n    check_interval_sec"},"when_requested":{"title":"when_requested","type":"object","properties":{"strategy_name":{"title":"Strategy Name","enum":["when_requested"],"type":"string","const":"when_requested"}},"description":"when_requested  - Strategy\nDefault Strategy!\nBuffy will redownload the resource when the client requests the resource.\nThis is the most simple scenario which is closest to a classic just-download case but with a fallback safeguard;\nIf the remote resource fails to download, buffy can fallback to an older cached version of the resource, if available."}}},"tags":[{"name":"Request","description":"Request a remote HTTP resource. Buffy will download this resource in the background and provide it via the `../response/` path"},{"name":"Response","description":"The metadata of a Request outcome. The `../content` of a result can be a json document, a file, a binary file or whatever you requested :)"}]}